text: Gyachung Kang is a mountain in the Himalayas range, in Nepal and China. It is the 15th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Yukihiko Kato, Kiyoto Sakaizawa, and Sirdar Pasang Putra Three, in 1964. ==References== Category:Mountains of China Category:Mountains of Nepal Category:Himalayas
title: Gyachung Kang
